content.description: Joey and Janine’s, Chandler knocks on the front door. Joey answers the door.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Hi, my name’s Chandler. I just moved in next door and I was wondering if you would be interested in battling me in a post-apoplectic world for control of the galaxies last remaining energy source?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Sure, neighbor come on in.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: So, is Janine around?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Uh, no, she’s at dance class.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Can I check out what she did to my room?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah, but, hey look, don’t go through her stuff. She gets really mad.(Chandler gives him a look and walks to the door of his old room.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh my God. What is th… it’s like a guy never lived in here. Look, you’ve got to be careful. This girl thing is dangerous. (Looking around the living room.) It’s spreading already.
content.parenthetical: The room is filled with flowers and a floral print sheet on the bed.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: It is???

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Yeah, is this your pretty pink pillow on the couch?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Is that your tiny little box, that’s too small to put anything in?
content.parenthetical: Pointing to the table and picking up the box.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: No! Ok, this is not good. You are a guy. Ok? This is a guys place. If you let this go, you’re going to be sitting around with your fingers soaking in stuff.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: All right, you’re right. I’ll talk to her.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Yes talk to her. Be a man.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I’m a man.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Defend yourself.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hmm. (Monica opens the front door and comes in.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Chandler come on. We have to hem the new dust ruffle.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Be right there sweetums. (Monica leaves. To Joey.) A totally different situation.

content.description: Central Perk, The gangs all here. Monica is walking in.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hey guys.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Hey, how was your breakfast with Hillary?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: It was okay. She’s still kind of depressed because she broke up with her boyfriend.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Ohh, yeah.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Well, is this Hillary your HOT assistant chef Hillary?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Yeah.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: The one that always stares at me when I come in?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: No, the one who looked at you once because you got in her way.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Still I could tell. She was into me. (Joey rolls his eyes.) Well, why don’t you set us up?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Ohh, are you setting Ross up with someone? Does she have a wedding dress?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Rachel?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: I’m, uhh, making up flyers trying to get new massage clients. So, can I come to Bloomingdale’s and use the copy machine.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Well, sure, but they might think it’s kinda weird considering I don’t work there anymore.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh my God. What happened?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I-I, got a job at Ralph Lauren.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well that’s great! Congratulations!! (She hugs Rachel.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah. (chuckling) A year ago..

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: You’ve lasted a whole year. Good for you.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: But, Pheebs, you can still use the copy machine where I actually work. But, just come by at lunch so my boss doesn’t see you. Cause Kim will just freak out and she already doesn’t like me very much.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: That’s weird. I don’t think my boss likes me either.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: I don’t think mine likes me either.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Maybe it’s a universal thing?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Or maybe, it’s because you’re hanging around here at 11:30 on a Wednesday. (Everybody gets up.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Yeah let’s head off to work.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: We should go.

content.description: Rachel’s office, Phoebe hands Rachel a key card.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Thank you.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Sure.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Now you will not believe this. But, I was in the copy room, making copies, and Ralph Lauren came in.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh my God. Did you talk to him?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yeah a little. He seems really nice. Good kisser.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: What? What!?! You kissed him?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Totally.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Phoebe are you serious?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yeah. I was just in there. He introduced himself and the next thing I know, we’re making out. You know.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Phoebe, I mean, you do know he’s married?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: No !

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Phoebe…

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: What am I supposed to do? Ask every guy I make out with if he’s married? (Rachel looks at her.) No, yeah, I should.

content.description: Joey and Janine’s apartment, Joey stares at a picture of a bay on the wall. Janine comes out of her room.

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: Hey Joey.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey. Uh, can I talk to you for a second? This, uh, kid in this picture. Do you, uh, know this kid? Is that like a relative or something?

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: No, I just thought it was cute.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah, that’s what I was afraid of.. Okay, uhh…Look Janine I really want you to feel at home here, but some of this new stuff. It’s…too girly.

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: Ohh. Like what?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Like this. (pointing to the picture) Pictures of cute babies we don’t know. We..we can’t have that.

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: Joey, it’s Anne Geddes. She’s a famous artist.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Look I don’t know this baby. I don’t know if she’s a famous artist or not. You know, and I don’t want to be a jerk but you’re changing too much around here.

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: Well, I’m sorry. I just thought I’d try to make the place a little nicer.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah but it’s too much stuff. You know like, you got the candles and the foofy schmoofer thing here and over here you got a picture of a watering can.

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: Well I just thought…

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I’m sure it’s a famous watering can, okay. But, come on…and what is with the really hot stick in the bathroom?

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: It’s a curling iron.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Ohh, well, that’s ok then. But, okay my towels for instance. I come in to the bathroom here and my towel is not on the floor where keep it. It’s up here on some hook..and…smells different.

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: It’s clean.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah, well, it feels different.

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: It’s dry.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Alright, I can make my peace with the clean dry towels…Also what is with these chips you bought?

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: No no no no, it’s potpourri. You’re supposed to smell it. (Joey takes a big whiff of the potpourri.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Well that’s like summer in a bowl.

content.description: Elevator at the Ralph Lauren offices, Rachel gets on her boss Kim is there.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh, Kim, Hi. (Kim doesn’t even look up from her report.)

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Uhh-huh.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: So you know, I…I handed in that marketing report and I never got to hear what you thought.

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: I didn’t read it.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Ahh…So…Wow…The spring line, it’s really going to be great this year, huh?

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Yeah.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: So I hear the Ralph Lauren fooled around with someone in the copy room. (Kim stops the elevator and turns to Rachel.)

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Tell me everything.

content.description: [Scene; Central Perk, Monica and Chandler are on the couch. Ross walks in.]

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hey guys.

content.speaker: Chandler and Monica
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What’s up? (He smiles. His teeth are freakishly white.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: You know…Oh My God.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: What happened to your teeth.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I whitened them.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Really.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah. What do you think.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Well, I think I shouldn’t look directly at them.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Come on, seriously.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Ross they’re really, really, really white.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Yeah, what was wrong with your old…human teeth.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Ahh, I-I did leave the gel on a little longer then it said to.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: How much longer?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: A-A day.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Ross you know that tonight is your date with Hillary?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I know. That’s why I did it. (With a big smile) Come on, are they really that bad?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: No, no no no. You’ll be fine. (turning to Monica) Hillary’s bind, right?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: She will be after tonight.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Yeah. (Rachel walks in.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh, hey, hey Rach, do you notice anything..ahh…

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah. Your teeth? Yes, I saw them from outside. (Sitting down on the couch.) You guys are never going to believe this. But, Phoebe made out with Ralph Lauren.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: What???

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Oh my god.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah I know. She ran into him at my office and they just…made out. And the craziest thing is, now my boss likes me because I told her about it and she said it was the best gossip she’d heard all year.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: I am proud of all my friends today.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: My God, Rachel, I can’t believe Phoebe made out with Ralph Lauren. Ohh, I’m so jealous. (Chandler looks at her.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Hi, I’m Chandler. Your live-in boy

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Chandler, please, come on. Look at him. (Pointing to a picture of Ralph on a magazine,.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh, I am no women, but that is one tasty dish. (Phoebe walks in.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Hey. Here. (Hands Chandler a copy of her flyer and sees the picture of Ralph.) Ohh, who’s the silver fox?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: That-that is your make out buddy. Don’t you recognize him? (Holding up the magazine in front of her face.) Oh wait. Ohh, Phoebe I love you. Kiss me please.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: That’s not Ralph Lauren. Sounds like him though.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yeah, no, Ralph doesn’t look anything like that guy. He’s-he’s young and he’s got long hair and a beard and a hacky sack.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh My God, Phoebe, that’s not Ralph Lauren. That’s Kenny the copy guy.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh..Go..Oh..and I told my boss that someone made out with Ralph Lauren. If she finds out that I lied to her, she is going to hate me even more. Phoebe !!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Why would the copy guy say he was Ralph Lauren?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: To get you to make out with him!!!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Ohhh.

content.description: Ross’s Apartment, Ross and Monica are there.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Okay, maybe this will make your teeth look less white. (Ross has a big smile.) Nope. Okay, colors that don’t work are blue, yellow, green, red, black, white, orange, and purple.
content.parenthetical: Holding a shirt in front of Ross.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I don’t know what I’m going to do. That date starts in like an hour.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hey Ross, maybe if your skin was lighter. Your teeth wouldn’t look so bright.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh great. So all I need to do is get some new skin. Thank you.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: I’m just saying, if we put just a little bit of makeup on you.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Whoa. Whoa. Whoa. We’re not 13 anymore.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Ross this is the only thing left that has a shot at working.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: But, won’t she notice I have makeup on?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Please. Half the guys out there have makeup on.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What??

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: All right, half the people. I mean, just try it and see.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No. I am not putting on makeup. (Knock at the door. Phoebe enters.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Hello. Oh good. Ross could you put up some of these flyers for me? (He smiles at her.) OH!! Demon!! Demon!!

content.description: Chandler’s and Monica’s apartment, Chandler and Monica are sitting at the kitchen table making potpourri sachets.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Now are drawers will smell nice and we didn’t waste these pantyhose.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Yes, God forbid we throw out old underwear. You-you know what? I’m going to go over to Joey’s.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Wait, we’re supposed to organize the wrapping paper drawer.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Yes, but I feel like I’ve really gotten in touch with my feminine side enough today. You know. In fact I think we’re two sachets away from becoming a lesbian couple.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: You know what? This has been kind of a girlie day. You’re right, I’m sorry.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Nah, Nah, it’s okay. I feel like I need to be in guy place. You know, do kind of like a man thing.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Yeah. Go over to Joey’s. Go over to Joey’s and drink some beer and hammer up some drywall.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: You know when guys hang out they don’t just drink some beer and hammer up drywall?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: When girls hang out, we don’t have pillow fights in our underwear. (Chandler gets a hurt look on his face.) I’m sorry. We do. We do. I don’t know why I said that.

content.description: Joey and Janine’s apartment, Chandler walks in. Joey and Janine are knitting at the kitchen counter.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey Chandler. Come on in. We’re knitting pot holders.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: No thanks, Josephine.

content.description: Ross’s apartment, Chandler enters. Ross is putting on makeup.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Hey Ross, I was wondering if… Oh my God !! Where are all the men???

content.description: Elevator at the Ralph Lauren offices, Kim’s waiting for it. The door opens and Rachel is inside.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Ohh, hi, Kim.

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Hi Rachel.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah, remember that thing I told you that happened yesterday? Well it didn’t happen.

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: You didn’t cancel the fabric order from Taiwan?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay, two things didn’t happen. Remember I told you that someone made out with Ralph Lauren in the copy room? Well, it turns out that’s not true.

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: That’s not true?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: No.

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Oh that’s interesting? Because I checked and only one keycard was used to access the copy machine yesterday during lunch and that keycard belonged to you, Rachel.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh no, no, no. Oh God, you think I made out with him.

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Listen to me. If you think sleeping with Ralph is going to get you my job. You are sadly mistaken.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I-I don’t want your job. I-I don’t. Ohh this is such a mistake. I did not make out with him. Nobody made out with him. I did not use my keycard yesterday. I don’t even know how to use my keycard. (The elevator stops. Ralph steps on.)

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Hi Ralph.

content.speaker: Ralph Lauren:
content.text: Hi Kim. (Dead silence until Ralph gets off the elevator.)

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Yeah, nothing happen. You could cut the sexual tension in here with a knife.

content.description: Hillary’s apartmen,. Hillary and Ross are having dinner. He is avoiding opening his mouth.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: And after that, what could I do except become a chef.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Mmm-Hmm.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: And someday soon, I hope to open my own restaurant.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Mmm.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: You know, you’re a really great listener. Most guys I go out with, they just talk and talk.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Mm-Hmm.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: After a while it’s like, shut your mouth, you know?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hmm-Hmm.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: I’ve probably been talking too much. Why don’t we talk about you a little bit?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Mmm-Unmm.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: Come on. I want to know.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hmm-Hmm-Hmm. (Putting his hand up to block his mouth.) Okay. I, uh, am from Long Island. I-I came to the city for college. Um, I, um, have a 5 year old son and in my spare time I like to read spy novels. But, but, let’s talk more about you. Hmm.

content.description: Joey and Janine’s apartment, Joey and Monica are arranging flowers. Chandler walks in.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: So what’s really neat. If you sear the stems of the flowers first in a frying pan, your arrangement will look fresh much longer.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Oh my God, Joey, that is such a great tip.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Monica, could you excuse us for a second? I need to talk to the girl with the flowers.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Okay. Oh but Joey, come over later because I’m going to teach you to make a bird feeder out of just a pine cone and some peanut butter.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Ohh, I love birds. (Monica leaves. Chandler shuts the door.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: What is the matter with you ?!?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: You’re arranging flowers! (Pointing to the dish on the table.) You got dead flowers! You got a picture, a picture, of a baby dressed like flowers! This is not Joey!!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey. Hey look I am still Joey, okay. Flowers they’re just, you know, they’re nice to look at. And that happens to be a picture by a famous artist. Of a famous baby.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: You’re turning into a women.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No I’m not. Why would you say that? That’s just mean.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Now I’ve upset you? What did I say?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: It’s not what you said. It’s the way you said it…Oh My God, I’m a women!!!

content.description: Central Perk, Phoebe and Rachel are there.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Now, she thinks that I made out with him and I did it to get her job.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: But why didn’t you just tell her the truth.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I did but she doesn’t think anyone would be stupid enough to confuse Kenny the copy guy with Ralph Lauren.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well, hey, what if Kenny were the real brains behind the whole company? You know. What if Kenny hired that Ralph Lauren guy to be the pretty front man? Huh, did she ever think of that?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: You were with Kenny today, weren’t you?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Just for a second.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Ohh, Phoebe, what am I going to do?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well, the only thing you can do. Sleep with Ralph Lauren.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: I’m not going to sleep with Ralph Lauren. I mean, I could, but I wouldn’t.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Ohh, sleep with Kenny.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: That wouldn’t help me.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Ohh, yes it would.

content.description: Hillary’s apartment, Hillary and Ross are finishing up their date.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: I’ve had a really good time tonight.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Mmm.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: You know, I rarely connect with someone this much on the first date.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hmm-Hmm-Hmm. (Picking up a piece of bread and covering his mouth.) Me, neither. I’ve had a really good time too, you know. (Putting the bread down.)

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: Are you going to eat that bread?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Ohh, I just like the smell. (Sniffing it.) Mmmm.
content.parenthetical: Putting the bread up to his nose.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: You make me laugh.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hmm-Hmm.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: Would you like to move over to the couch?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Mmm-Hmm. (Picking up their wine glasses.)

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: Maybe I’ll just turn the lights down a little.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: How about all the way.
content.parenthetical: Covering his mouth with the glass.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: Okay. (She goes to turn the lights off and Ross sits on the couch. She has some black light posters on the wall.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Wow, cool poster. Or should I say groovy poster? (They sit down on the couch. Ross smiles and the black light fluoresces his teeth.) So, ahh, where were we?

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: Are those your teeth??

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Ohh, you can see them, huh?

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: Yes. They’re insanely white.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: I-I, did that for you.

content.speaker: Hillary
content.text: What’s a matter with you?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What’s a matter with me? You’ve got a black light. It’s 1999!

content.description: Elevator at the Ralph Lauren Offices, Rachel gets in . Kim is there.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Kim, hi.

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Hi Rachel. Ohh, I’ve been meaning to ask you. Have you seen the new Ralph Lauren sheets? Ohh, what am I thinking. Of course you have.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay..Okay.. Look. I’m sorry that I lied to you before. You were right. Ralph and I were an item but were not anymore.

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Oh, really?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah, he dumped me. He said, “Rachel, I can’t do this. Even though you are a very, very, very beautiful women. I can’t do this. I’m married and I’m sorry.” And then I don’t know why but he said, “and you will never get promoted. Especially not above Kim, who is an integral cog in the Ralph Lauren machine.”

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: You expect me to believe..(Doors open, Ralph steps in.) Hi Ralph.

content.speaker: Ralph Lauren:
content.text: Hi Kim. (Dead silence again until he gets off.)

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Oh my God. He just gave you the coldest look I have ever seen. It’s like he hates you. Then it is true.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Of course it’s true and it hurts so bad.

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Ohh honey come here. (Hugging Rachel.) Ohh it will be ok. We’ve all been there.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: You and Ralph?

content.speaker: Kim
content.text: Kenny the copyboy.

content.description: Joey and Janine’s apartment, Joey paces the floor waiting for Janine. She walks in.

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey, uhh, I need to talk to you.

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: What’s the matter? Are you upset?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I’m sorry but we’ve got to get rid of all this girlie stuff in here. I, uh, I got to be a man! Okay. The living room has to remain a guy place, okay? That’s just the way it has to be.

content.speaker: Janine
content.text: Well, if that’s what you want. I’ll just put it all in my room.

content.speaker: Joey
